720931f-a.text:
Lexington Avenue, north from East 26th Street, showing an early view of this arterial thoroughfare. Note the street-cartracks. These were removed (by the C. W. A.) and service continued by busses.
April 13, 1924
Standard Photographic Service
Gift of Borough President of Manhattan

East 26th Street, north side, between Lexington and Fourth Avenue's, showing the finished front of a renovation job to several former brownstone buildings.

Lexington Ave., at the N.W corner of East 26th Street.  Also shown is East 26th Street, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Lexington Ave.
